    <!-- Filter Help -->
    <string name="filter_help_title">About Filter Types</string>
    <string name="filter_help_content">
<b>KEYWORD BASED</b><br/>
Searches for specific words or phrases in SMS content.<br/>
Example: Block SMS containing \"bank\"<br/><br/>

<b>SENDER NUMBER</b><br/>
Filters SMS from specific phone numbers.<br/>
Example: Allow SMS from \"+905551234567\"<br/><br/>

<b>WHITELIST</b><br/>
Only forwards SMS from allowed senders.<br/>
Example: Only forward SMS containing \"John\" or \"Work\"<br/><br/>

<b>BLACKLIST</b><br/>
Blocks SMS from specific senders.<br/>
Example: Block SMS containing \"Ads\" or \"Spam\"<br/><br/>

<b>SIM BASED</b><br/>
Determines which SIM card SMS should be processed from.<br/>
Examples:<br/>
• \"slot:0\" - Only SMS from SIM 1<br/>
• \"turkcell\" - SMS from Turkcell SIM<br/>
• \"vodafone\" - SMS from Vodafone SIM<br/><br/>

<b>ACTION TYPES:</b><br/>
• <b>ALLOW:</b> Forward SMS if filter matches<br/>
• <b>BLOCK:</b> Block SMS if filter matches<br/><br/>

<b>REGEX:</b> You can use regex for advanced pattern matching.
    </string>
    
